JetBrains Rider 2019.2 Help

Access Decompiled Files

All decompiled code that you can see in the editor is actually decompiled to temporary files. You can access these files if necessary.

To access decompiled files

  • To display the current file in its containing folder, right-click the editor tab header and choose Show in Explorer/Finder.

  • To copy the path to the current file, right-click the editor tab header and choose Copy Path Ctrl+Shift+C or Copy Relative Path Ctrl+Shift+Alt+C.

  • You can also add the decompiled document to the favorites list for further reference — right-click the editor tab header and choose Add to favorites.

If at any point you’d like to clear the decompilation cache, you can remove the data in %USERPROFILE%\.Rider2019.2\config\resharper-host\DecompilerCache.
